HEADWORD: Collenchyma
<hw>Col*len"chy*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>ko`lla</grk> glue + <?/ an infusion. Formed like
<ets>parenchyma</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tissue of
vegetable cells which are thickend at the angles and (usually)
elongated.</def>⟦br⟧
